At Ocasta, we help you prove the guess wrong — kindly — with evidence.

Dataviva offers next generation retail planning and supply chain solutions on a unified, real-time platform. Our platform allows for automating decision-making and massively reducing user workload. Our team has delivered planning systems for some of the world’s leading retailers; we know that retailers need flexible, scalable planning that deploys quickly and can be adapted as the business evolves and faces new challenges. 

Our solutions:

  • Demand Forecasting: our algorithms can identify patterns from historical sales enabling automated new item forecasting that doesn’t require picking like items, automated size curves, and improved promotional forecasting calculations
  • Supply Chain: time-phased SCP that accounts for all supply chain constraints for the foreseeable planning horizon
  • Merchandise & Assortment: recommends the optimal number of choices per channel and provides automated, strategy-driven approaches for building the assortment wedge
  • Price & Promotion: provides unified, full-lifecycle price and promotion planning solution including automated price changes, regular and promotion price optimization, and full promotion planning

headline: VP, Global Business Development - FreedomPay
summary:
Hi! I’m Court! 💁🏻‍♀️

Here at FreedomPay, we offer the worlds largest, processor agnostic, payment orchestration platform.  I am all about helping merchants, processors and technology providers optimize their payments infrastructure to grow revenue! 

Payment Orchestration = Flexibility. Optionality. Growth. 🤑

In today’s rapidly evolving business environment, adaptability isn’t just a competitive advantage—it’s a necessity. That’s where Payment Orchestration comes in, and it’s why solutions like FreedomPay’s Omnichannel Gateway are a game-changer.

At its core, payment orchestration is about empowering businesses with the flexibility and optionality to design the payment ecosystem that best suits their needs. Whether it’s delivering a seamless experience across in-store, online, and mobile channels, or quickly integrating new technologies and payment methods, the right orchestration platform transforms how businesses operate.

💡 Here’s why this matters:

✅ Flexibility to scale: Expand into new markets or channels without worrying about outdated payment infrastructure.

✅ Optionality to innovate: Choose from a vast network of acquirers, processors, and payment methods. 

✅ Seamless customer experience: Unify payment processes across every touchpoint or selling system, eliminating friction and boosting satisfaction.

FreedomPay’s Omnichannel Gateway stands out because it’s more than just a solution—it’s a strategy for growth. It empowers merchants with unparalleled control, agility, and the ability to future-proof their payment stack.

If you’re navigating the complex world of payments and looking for a smarter way to connect and optimize and maximze your revenue potential, I encourage you to stop by our booth #4775 or lets schedule a meeting! 

Looking forward to seeing you in the big 🍎!

name: Elool Jacoby
headline: CPO - Notch
summary:
I’m Elool Jacoby, CPO and co-founder at Notch. We build AI agents that automate and augment customer support for mid-market and enterprise teams, helping them handle high ticket volumes with better accuracy, safety, and customer experience. Our focus is deploying AI that is production-ready, configurable, and trusted by support and operations teams.

I’m attending NRF to learn how leading retailers are using AI in customer service, especially how they scale support during peak demand, improve resolution quality, and integrate AI into existing workflows. I’m also interested in how retail organizations are approaching governance, safety, and human-in-the-loop models as AI becomes more customer-facing.

I’m excited to connect with retail and ecommerce leaders, CX and support executives, and teams exploring AI-driven automation, as well as technology partners and platforms in the customer support ecosystem. If you’re thinking about how to responsibly scale customer support with AI, I’d love to connect.

name: Gil Dror
headline: Chief Technology Officer - SmartSense by Digi
summary:
Greetings,
As we approach the National Retail Federation show, I would like to extend an invite to colleagues with a technical inclination or those involved in innovation within the retail space.

I specialize in the application of SmartSense technologies — leveraging IoT, machine learning, and advanced analytics to empower retailers to make informed, data-driven decisions. Our solutions are crafted to ensure operational efficiency, reduce waste, and enhance both the in-store and backend aspects of retail management.

I am interested in meeting individuals who are:

- Technical Experts: If you have a background in developing or implementing technical solutions for retail, and are interested in exchanging insights or discussing advancements in IoT and analytics, a conversation with you would be beneficial.

- Innovation Leaders: For those responsible for driving innovation in retail, particularly if you are looking to improve operational efficiency and customer experience through data insights, I believe a discussion around SmartSense's capabilities could be of value.

If your objectives align with creating a more efficient, data-enhanced retail environment, I welcome the opportunity to connect during NRF to see how we can work together towards common goals.

Feel free to reach out to me through the NRF portal or directly contact me to arrange a meeting.
